OL,3,CMurdered woman's mother welcomes call
OL,4,Cto rethink killer's release
OL,6,FFollowing his fifth parole hearing,
OL,7,FLing was recommended for release into
OL,8,Fthe community, subject to conditions
OL,9,Fincluding informing authorities of any
OL,10,Frelationships he might develop; being
OL,11,Fsubject to monitoring and a curfew,
OL,12,Fand remaining outside an exclusion
OL,13,Fzone to avoid contact with his
OL,14,Fvictim's family.
OL,16,FThe Justice Secretary and Lord
OL,17,FChancellor Shabana Mahmood has now
OL,18,Fasked the Parole Board to reconsider
OL,19,Fthe recommendation to release him on
OL,20,Fthe basis that it was 'legally
OL,21,Firrational'.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/7
