OL,3,CMurdered woman's mother welcomes call
OL,4,Cto rethink killer's release
OL,6,FA charge of rape was left on file
OL,7,Fduring the original court case, so he
OL,8,Fis not a convicted sex offender.
OL,9,FHowever in its ruling the Parole Board
OL,10,Fsaid: "Mr Ling has always accepted
OL,11,Fthat he raped the victim."
OL,13,FDuring sentencing, Mr Justice Potts
OL,14,Ftold Ling, who was 23 at the time of
OL,15,Fthe murder, "You will never be
OL,16,Freleased so long as it is thought you
OL,17,Fconstitute a danger to women." He was
OL,18,Fgiven life with a minimum term of 20
OL,19,Fyears, which was reduced to 18 years
OL,20,Fby the High Court.
