OL,4,Cto rethink killer's release
OL,6,FThe panel accepted that Ling
OL,7,Fundertaken an official programme to
OL,8,Faddress his violent and sexual
OL,9,Foffending, and his conduct in prison
OL,10,F"has largely been exemplary".
OL,12,FDuring a hearing in July 2024, two
OL,13,Fpsychologists agreed he should be
OL,14,Ffreed from prison saying he felt
OL,15,Fashamed of his "monstrous" past.
OL,17,FThe Lord Chancellor said: "My thoughts
OL,18,Fremain with the family and friends of
OL,19,FJoanne Tulip, whose life was taken in
OL,20,Fa truly horrifying attack.
